overview:
The Dublin Web Summit brings some of the worldâ€™s leading tech entrepreneurs, investors, media and business leaders to Ireland to speak to the start up and business communities. The Summit is a learning and networking event that attracts an average of 700 attendees at each event.

In 2010, the inaugural year of Dublin Web Summit, the founders of Youtube, Twitter and Skype were amongst over 100 speakers drawn from around the world. Over 2,500 people attended our Summits in 2010, which have been covered by leading international media including Bloomberg, The New York Times, CNBC, The Telegraph, The Irish Times, RTE and many more. This year Dublin Web Summit is poised to become Europe’s premier web and tech event, attracting top quality speakers, the industry’s most influential investors and the world’s most promising start-ups.
